    <h1>Image URL Analyzer API Documentation</h1>
    <p><strong>Overview:</strong> This API analyzes a given URL to determine if it points to an image.</p>
    <p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>/answers/:image_url</code></p>
    <p><strong>Example usage with curl:</strong></p>
    <pre>
        curl -X GET 'http://localhost:3000/answers?image_url=https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2015/04/23/22/00/tree-736885_640.jpg'
    </pre>
    <p><strong>Possible Responses:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>{"message": "This is an image"}</code> - If the URL points to an image.</li>
      <li><code>{"message": "This is not an image"}</code> - If the URL does not point to an image.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Error Codes:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>400 Bad Request</code> - If the URL parameter is missing or incorrect.</li>
    </ul>
